<br>
Which firewall are you using (I'm assuming it's software)?  I'm not familiar with WinXP's built in system, but in some, like ZoneAlarm, you can bypass the firewall to/from certain IPs only, so you just input in the iP address of the patch and game servers and you should be all set. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugolsec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Golsec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/3/01 4:18:05 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/zidane2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Everquest behind WinXP/2K's ICS</span><hr size=1> First of all... seems the WinXP/2K ICS isn't what's causing the zone-boot syndrome this time, so all is well :)  You're right, the new version doesn't mess with EQ any more.<br>
A lot of people are having the problem.. looks like it might be yet another bug from all these patches.<br>
<br>
Hehe, we do have a Zyxel router, but... personally I prefer software ones.  You can see what's happening (line traffic etc) on a monitor, and easily dial it up remotely without having to trust dial-on-demand (yuck)<br>
<br>
Thing is, thanks to Microshaft trying to monopolise things again, they've managed to nerf Gamevoice so that only one person behind a NAT can connect to a peer-hosted session... unless you use their own ICS (Gamevoice uses this new Universal Plug n Play thing of theirs)<br>
So to put it simply, it *must* be ICS.  Can't use anything else :(<br>
<br>
The built-in firewall is extremely simple.  It's a tickbox - on or off - that's it.  The ICS software has port forwarding, and seems to punch holes in the firewall when it needs them for that, but otherwise it isn't customisable.<br>
<br>
I'll be trying Tiny Personal Firewall this aft, since it seems to work with ICS *touch wood* anything has to be better than that built-in thing. <p>-- <br>
